# Aigent.ly — implementation alignment

## Source of truth
- Product behavior, IA, components, and v1 scope: repo `prd.md` (treat as authoritative).
- Visual references only: `stitch_prototype/` (HTML + Tailwind CDN + DESIGN tokens). Do not copy CDN Tailwind or prototype-only fonts/icons as the production pattern unless explicitly asked.

## Stack (do not drift)
- Framework: Next.js 15, App Router, TypeScript strict.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4, utility-first; shadcn/ui; Lucide; Geist via `next/font` (fallback Inter per PRD).
- Content: MDX for rules/learn; static JSON for threats (no live CVE API in v1).
- Search/state: Fuse.js (client), nuqs (URL state), Zustand + localStorage for ratings v1.
- Other PRD libs as specified: Shiki, next-mdx-remote, Framer Motion (light), sonner, next-themes.

## V1 boundaries (do not add without explicit approval)
- No user authentication or accounts.
- No backend API or database for v1; no CMS — everything static or localStorage.
- No on-site community submission form (GitHub PR flow).
- Defer: payments, email newsletter, social login, real-time CVE feeds.

## Performance / UX (from PRD)
- Prefer SSG: `generateStaticParams` for rule listings where applicable.
- Lighthouse-oriented: next/image with dimensions, next/font, client-side filters without API round-trips.
- Accessibility: keyboard, ARIA on icon buttons, focus rings, skip link.

## Hosting: Hostinger (production)
- Deploy to Hostinger (Node Web App Git deploy or VPS); use platform `PORT` for `next start` when applicable.
- Do not rely on Vercel-only services in production: replace `@vercel/analytics` with a Hostinger-compatible alternative or omit in v1; do not depend on Vercel KV for core flows.
- Avoid Edge-only Next features for critical v1 paths unless confirmed supported on the chosen Hostinger runtime; prefer Node runtime or static generation.

## Repo layout
- Prefer monorepo shape from PRD: `apps/web` as the Next app with `app/` routes matching PRD tree.

## When unsure
- Re-read `prd.md` sections for the feature; if still ambiguous, ask the user before expanding scope.